<HEAD>Trucks Collide and Catch Fire; Butter Cargo Melts Onto California
Interstate</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BAKER, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two tractor-trailers, one loaded with
butter, collided and burst into flames on Interstate 15, killing one
driver and greasing the desert roadway with melted butter, officials
said.
   The accident happened Thursday night in a northbound lane
reserved for trucks ascending a grade of Interstate 15, said Highway
Patrol spokesman Antonio Gonzalez.
   One rig rear-ended the other 17 miles north of this desert
community and 150 miles northeast of Los Angeles, according to
Gonzalez.
   The highway, made slick by butter melted in the fire, was closed
about 15 minutes. One lane was reopened, and state Department of
Transportation workers coated the other lanes with sand.
   The name of the driver killed in the accident was not immediately
available.
  
