<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Indonesia-Earthquake     12-30 0155</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Indonesia-Earthquake,0159</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Earthquake Jolts Indonesia</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: One name for Setianto in 3rd graf is cq</NOTE>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A strong earthquake rocked the
northeastern coastal city of Jayapura today, panicking residents but
causing no serious damage, the official Antara news agency reported.
   The quake, measuring 5.7 on the Richter scale, occurred at about
9:30 a.m., Antara said. It said the earthquake sent many city
residents into a panic, particularly those working on the upper
floors of tall buildings.
   Antara quoted Setianto, provincial chief of the Meteorology and
Geophysics Agency, as saying the quake's epicenter was about 60
miles from Jayapura, the capital of Irian Jaya province.
   There were no immediate reports of serious damage or casualties,
the news agency said.
   An earthquake measuring 5 on the Richter scale can cause serious
damage in populated areas. Every increase of one number in the scale
indicates a tenfold increase in the magnitude of the quake.
</TEXT>
