<HEAD>25 Hurt in Ferry Accident; Death Toll in Earlier Sinking 73</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities recovered 44 more bodies
from a sunken ferry on Friday, raising the death toll from the
accident to at least 73, police said.
   The ferry capsized Tuesday about six miles south of Dhaka. At
least 30 passengers on the vessel still were missing.
   Also Friday, a ferry with 200 passengers on board capsized in
southeastern Bangladesh and at least 25 passengers were injured,
police said.
   Friday's ferry accident occured near Chittagong, 135 miles
southeast of Dhaka. The boat was carrying Moslem pilgrims and sank
after striking sunken debris, police said.
