<HEAD>Four Burmese Fishermen Drift To Sri Lanka</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLOMBO, Sri Lanka (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four Burmese fishermen adrift on the
high seas for 40 days have landed safely in northeastern Sri Lanka,
about 1,100 miles away, authorities said Friday.
   The fishermen landed Thursday in the coastal village of
Mullaitivu, about 170 miles northeast of Colombo, police said.
   One police officer, speaking on condition of anonymity, said the
fishermen would be taken to Colombo and turned over to the Burmese
Embassy.
   The officer said the four men had been drifting since their
fishing boat developed engine trouble in mid-November off Burma. He
said the four survived by eating raw fish.
