<HEAD>Bomb Kills Man At Amusement Park</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KARACHI, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A homemade bomb exploded in a crowded
amusement park Friday, killing a young man and injuring four other
people, police said.
   People fled in panic from the Funland park near the Clifton Beach
recreational area. The blast left a hole about a foot deep and a
foot wide.
   The dead man was not identified but appeared to be about 20 years
old, police said, speaking on condition of anonymity.
   There was no immediate indication of who was responsible for the
6:15 p.m. blast. The explosion occurred on the Islamic faith's
weekly day of rest, a time when the park is crowded with
lower-income families.
   The site was about one mile from Prime Minister Benazir Bhutto's
family residence.
