<1ST_LINE>r a AM-KitchenKilling     12-30 0246</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Kitchen Killing,0253</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman Preparing Dinner Killed By Shots Fired Through Window</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunman lurking in an alley fired shots
through the kitchen window of an adjacent house, killing a woman as
she prepared dinner for her mother, police said.
   Sandra Davidson, 25, was struck in the head Wednesday as she
stood next to the sink opening a can of vegetables in her South
Central Los Angeles home, said Detective Adalberto Luper.
   A male friend of Ms. Davidson who was in the kitchen with her was
unhurt, police said. Family members identified him as Mike, a
homeless man whom Ms. Davidson occasionally invited in for a hot
meal or a couch to sleep on.
   ``Basically, we haven't determined if they were after him or
her,'' Luper said. ``That's still pending at this point.''
   The family said the attackers may have been gang members, but
police said they were not investigating the slaying as a
gang-related homicide. The neighborhood is a high crime area.
   Powder burns around the bullet holes on the window screen
indicated the shots were fired at close range from the alley just
outside the window, police said.
   Relatives remembered Ms. Davidson as friendly and outgoing.
   ``She was a sweet child, she didn't bother no one,'' said her
mother, Louise Davidson, 66.
   ``She's too beautiful to be dead,'' said her brother Thomas
Davidson, 27. ``We used to go fishing on the weekends. We were going
to go this weekend.''
</TEXT>
