   Count Prince Charles out this year, but Sweden's
king and Britain's Sting are among the rich and famous who have
gathered at Swiss alpine resorts for the New Year's holiday.
   King Carl XVI Gustaf, Queen Silvia and their three children were
among the early arrivals at Klosters, in the Grisons. Britain's
Prince Charles has sent word, however, that he will not take his
skiing holiday in Klosters until March.
   St. Moritz will again be able to boast the longest list of
