<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Billionaire developer Marvin Davis has found out
how slow the real estate market is in Denver.
   The Cherry Hills mansion Davis put on the market for $4.5 million
in the summer of 1987 has been sold to Denver developer Kal Zeff for
$1.725 million, officials confirmed Thursday.
   Zeff, owner of CDM Cos., one of the largest privately held
builders of homes and apartments in Denver, closed the deal Dec. 21.
The mansion includes such amenities as an indoor movie theater and
putting green.
