<HEAD>Real Sword Used By Mistake Seriously Injures Actor In Samurai Film</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An actor filming a samurai drama was seriously
injured in a battle scene when a real sword was substituted
accidentally for a fake one, police said Friday.
   Yukio Kato was slashed in the neck during the filming of the
traditional Japanese movie on Monday, said Hiroshima Prefectural
Police.
   Kato, 34, was unconscious and in serious condition at Okayama
University Hospital, the police said.
   The real sword was to be used later in the film during a close-up
scene, according to a report by Kyodo News Service.
   A fake sword that was to have been used in the battle scene was
in poor condition, and the director of the movie, Shintaro Katsu,
ordered the crew to replace it with another, Kyodo said.
   It said the real sword was used for an extended period of time in
the filming before the injury occurred.
   Police said they seized the sword and the rolls of film
containing the battle scene and were questioning the movie crew.
