<HEAD>First Victim Of Year-End Mania</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CASERTA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A New Year's firecracker killed a man
Friday when the rocket he had made exploded, police said.
   Police have seized large amounts of fireworks throughout Italy in
an effort to prevent deaths and injuries.
   Two towns in northern Italy, near Bergamo, have issued decrees
banning traditional year-end celebrations involving the explosives.
