<1ST_LINE>r f PM-OilPrices     12-30 0157</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Oil Prices,0165</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Energy Futures Slip</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Energy futures prices fell amid profit-taking in
a lackluster yearend session.
   On the New York Mercantile Exchange Thursday, the February
contract for West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark grade of U.S.
crude oil, slipped 20 cents to settle at $16.77 a barrel. On
Wednesday, the contract edged up 2 cents.
   Among refined petroleum products traded on the exchange, the
January contract for wholesale home heating oil declined 0.72 cent
to 52.77 cents a gallon after falling 0.28 cent the previous session.
   January wholesale unleaded gasoline settled 0.03 cent lower to
close at 47.01 cents a gallon following a 0.43-cent drop on
Wednesday.
   Andrew Lebow, a senior broker and analyst E.D.&F. Man
International Futures Inc., said trading was dull, with
profit-taking responsible for the few price movements.
   The drop in heating oil prices resulted from an abundance of oil
in the spot market for the distillate, Lebow said.
</TEXT>
