<1ST_LINE>d f BC-Venezuela-Tariffs     12-30 0102</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Venezuela-Tariffs,0106</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Venezuela Imposes 60 Percent Tariff on Many Imports</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government declared a 60 percent
tariff Friday on luxury imports from countries outside Latin America
as a means to conserve foreign exchange.
   The presidential decree, published in the El Universal newspaper,
is effective for one year. It affects 500 imports, including
liquors, electronic and electrical machinery, insecticides and
luxury foodstuffs.
   Exempted from the tariff are those goods from Peru, Bolivia,
Ecuador and Colombia, and those subject to trade discussions within
the Latin American Integration Association, to which most nations in
Latin America and the Caribbean belong.
</TEXT>
